race.comment: The $1 million Fillies And Mares. JENNI THE FOX (4) saluted at Listed level last time out and will have taken a stack of confidence from that overdue victory. Gets gun hoop Williams on board from a low draw and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. IT'S A KNOCKOUT (6) resumes here but the form she showed when last in work was good enough for a race like this. Is yet to miss a quinella spot in three first-up attempts and a strong showing while fresh would not surprise. DANCE TO THE BOOM (1) will be better for that first-up Nudgee outing and has won when second-up before. Respect from the Baker yard. POSTER GIRL (9) has won three of her past four and is racing high on confidence of late. Has to be included. COUNTYOURBLESSINGS (5) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
